Hello Ruby.  It is interesting that you (and many others) see so much going on in the East Coast.  Would it surprise you that many states in the Northeast are gaining population at a much, much slower rate than states like Texas and Florida? In fact these states will likely lose representatives in Congress next year to some of the southern states.

Perhaps land development might be correlated to something else in addition to population growth?  What do you think?

